title: Bug 121170: get column label from meta data object should return some user recognizable strings
OB: When calling the 'get column label' function on the meta data object, the labels returned before extraction are null. However, after extraction, the labels are recognizable strings.
EB: The 'get column label' function should return user recognizable strings even before extraction.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Create a meta data object.
2. Call the 'get column label' function on the meta data object before extraction.
3. Note that the labels returned are null.
